#+DESCRIPTION: My pet Polish Club bidding system

* Introduction

Welcome to Chen-Pang He (jdh8)'s experimental Polish Club!
We use the distribution syntax and abbreviations provided by WBF.

http://www.worldbridge.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Guidetocompletion.pdf

The ACBL convention card of this system is at

https://bridgewinners.com/convention-card/print/polish-club-jdh8/98013

Polish Club is a 5-card major small club bidding system, where the 1!c opening
is forcing but not necessarily strong.  This bidding system is largely based on
/Polish Club 2020: Expert./  Changes are made with /Good, Better, Best/ and my
improvisation.

** Notable differences from /Polish Club 2020: Expert/

*** Constructive auctions

- We use natural 2/1.  1Y-2X are forcing to game.  1Y-3X are invitational jump
  shifts except 1!d-3!c.
- We use Truscott/Jordan 2NT.  1M-2NT is at least a 4-card limit raise.  1M-3M
  is a mixed raise.
- XYZ (two-way checkback) is only on after 1!c!d-1!h-1!s.  We use plain
  checkback in the other cases.

*** Preempts

- The 2M preempts contain balanced hands.  This treatment is proven useful in
  /Good, Better, Best./
- We modified continuations after the 2X preempts.
- Namyats replaces natural 4m.

*** Slam try

- We use kickback and exclusion RKCB 1430 for all suits.
- Uncovered by the book, we also suggest using the non-serious 3NT, Optional
  Minorwood, and Last Train in slam tries.

